postcontent:
Comes with [3] 30 round mags, [1] 5 round mag, and [300] rounds of Wolf 7.62x39 jacketed hollow point ammo (maybe more, I have to go look at the label on the ammo can).

Real deal this time. Last buyer flaked and I got burned out on the selling process for a while. 1800 or best offer takes the lot. I know the price might seem up there but this is an out of production SBR-ready rifle by Arsenal I haven't seen one actually sell for less than this in over a year: 

http://www.gunbroker.com/Auction/ViewItem.aspx?Item=320767915

Super-rare, high quality rifle from Arsenal, just begging to be SBR'd. I've had it for about 2 years and put MAYBE 200 rounds through it the whole time I've had it. It's a slick little gun but it just doesn't get that much love from me because my range time is usually dedicated to my build projects or handgun work. 

This gun is actually appreciating in value at a pretty steady rate, but I'm a project guy. I'd rather have some guns to tinker with than a pretty one that just sits in the safe, and really a fine machine like this should go to somebody who will actually fire it. At this point I'm just fielding offers to see if anybody is interested before the election makes everybody crazy. I'm happy to make a deal but I'm not in a rush to get rid of it. 

I prefer face to face but shipping is an option provided your FFL accepts transfers from private sellers.
